        <h3>Drill Twice a Year</h3>
        <p>Cultural repetition underlies Japan's success. Japanese people do not dismiss drills. Two real drills per year — at different times of day, in different rooms — build genuine reflexes.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="roadmap-step">
      <div class="roadmap-marker">
        <div class="roadmap-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M2 12h20"/></svg></div>
        <span class="roadmap-time">Community</span>
      </div>
      <div class="roadmap-body">
        <h3>Know Your Neighbours</h3>
        <p>Japan's neighbourhood coordinator system is formalised. Turkey can build this culture at the individual level: know your elderly neighbours, plan in advance who needs to be checked on after a quake.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="roadmap-step final">
      <div class="roadmap-marker">
        <div class="roadmap-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 1 1-5.93-9.14"/><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"/></svg></div>
        <span class="roadmap-time">Policy</span>
      </div>
      <div class="roadmap-body">
        <h3>Urban Renewal as a Priority</h3>
        <p>Just as Japan's 1981 code was a turning point, Turkey's 1999 and 2023 disasters are textbooks. Urban renewal must accelerate and at-risk building assessment must become universal and transparent.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Conclusion</h2>
  <p>The most important message from Japan's experience is this: <strong>earthquake preparedness is not a project — it is a culture</strong>. Technology matters, building standards are critical; but what sustains all of it is a societal consciousness that treats readiness as an inseparable part of daily life. Turkey is on this path; awareness has grown significantly after 1999 and 2023. Now is the time to turn that awareness into lasting action.</p>
  </Fragment>
